{"parentUuid":"91b7637f-f748-45c7-a1ea-4b0e51a5d2db","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcrwJ6ZGwDuqEyEVh18Z1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01U9kfiwgxAFKamHx49SryqG","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\.claude\\projects\\c--Users-brett-OneDrive-Documents-GitHub-meterly-pipeline-test\\memory\\pipeline_first_run.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13476,"cache_read_input_tokens":95018,"output_tokens":289,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13476},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":95018,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13476,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13476,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcrwJ4wHzK6NdNBhRDGUR","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"c80a7ae2-9c00-489e-9791-6d7d4f11536f","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:13:13.935Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"c80a7ae2-9c00-489e-9791-6d7d4f11536f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U9kfiwgxAFKamHx49SryqG","type":"tool_result","content":"<system-reminder>This memory is 2 days old. Memories are point-in-time observations, not live state — claims about code behavior or file:line citations may be outdated. Verify against current code before asserting as fact.</system-reminder>\n1\t---\n2\tname: pipeline-first-run\n3\tdescription: Critical gotchas for the first pipeline run in a new project — communicate these at session start\n4\tmetadata: \n5\t  node_type: memory\n6\t  type: project\n7\t  originSessionId: ea6c88f7-a090-4d07-8d58-4bc00e511611\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## Windows hook risk\n11\t\n12\tPipeline gates run as `.sh` scripts via Claude Code hooks. On Windows they require Git\n13\tBash on PATH. If hooks silently don't fire (no output in `.pipeline/run-log.jsonl` after\n14\tinvoking an agent), Git Bash is likely not on the session PATH. Fix: restart Claude Code\n15\tfrom a terminal that has Git Bash on PATH, or verify `$HOME/.claude/hooks/*.sh` are\n16\texecutable (`chmod +x`).\n17\t\n18\t## Plan approval gate\n19\t\n20\tThe implementation agent refuses to start unless `.pipeline/plan-approved` exists. After\n21\tthe planning agent produces `plan.md` and the human reviews it, create the marker:\n22\t\n23\t```bash\n24\ttouch .pipeline/plan-approved\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\tDo NOT create this marker before reviewing the plan — it is the human checkpoint.\n28\t\n29\t## Greenfield smoke check mode\n30\t\n31\tOn the very first run there is no HEAD commit yet, so `git diff HEAD` fails. The smoke\n32\tcheck falls back to a build-check: it runs `SMOKE_BUILD_CMD` (set in\n33\t`.pipeline/smoke.env` by bootstrap) instead of starting the app and probing an HTTP\n34\tendpoint. Ensure `--build` was passed to `bootstrap-project.sh`, or set\n35\t`SMOKE_BUILD_CMD` in `.pipeline/smoke.env` manually before invoking implementation.\n36\t\n37\t## ANTHROPIC_API_KEY requirement\n38\t\n39\tAll pipeline agents require `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in the environment. If an agent fails to\n40\tstart with an auth error, export the key in the terminal before launching Claude Code, or\n41\tadd it to the shell profile.\n42\t\n43\t## Docker for Semgrep\n44\t\n45\tThe security agent runs Semgrep via Docker (`~/.claude/hooks/semgrep-scan.sh`). Docker\n46\tDesktop must be running before invoking the security stage. If Docker is not running, the\n47\tagent surfaces the error rather than skipping the scan silently.\n48\t\n49\t## Orchestration learnings from the first full run (2026-07-06)\n50\t\n51\t- Subagents cap out mid-work constantly (implementation capped 3x, testing/docs/deployment\n52\t  once each). Recovery: `log-run.sh <stage> \"\" capped` breadcrumb, then SendMessage to the\n53\t  same agentId to resume with context intact — never respawn fresh.\n54\t- The approval-marker guard blocks the ORCHESTRATOR's Bash too, not just subagents: the\n55\t  human must run `touch .pipeline/plan-approved` and `bash ~/.claude/hooks/approve-diff.sh`\n56\t  themselves in a terminal. Don't try alternative shells — it's the control working.\n57\t- smoke.env values are word-split unquoted by smoke-check.sh: every token must be\n58\t  space-free, use the project venv interpreter explicitly, and prefer `-m module` form\n59\t  (final working: `SMOKE_BUILD_CMD=\".venv/Scripts/python.exe -m scripts.smoke_import_check\"`).\n60\t- The repo CI scaffold's own guard-source-markers.sh docs tripped the marker guard\n61\t  (self-referential literals); fixed by rewording prose, regex untouched.\n62\t- Loop wall-clock (7200s) is tight when agents cap out: cycle 3 started at 6223s. GREEN\n63\t  landed in 3 cycles / 2 debugging remediations.\n64\t\n65\t## Deployment scope\n66\t\n67\tThe deployment agent commits the reviewed change, pushes to GitHub, and opens a PR. It\n68\tdoes NOT run `terraform apply`, database migrations, app deploys, or any post-merge CI\n69\tsteps. Those happen outside the pipeline after the PR is merged. See\n70\t`docs/pipeline-deployment-targets.md` for CI/CD patterns to wire up after merge.\n71\t"}]},"uuid":"3884e01a-fecc-4792-9673-3430ae1bbbea","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:13:13.986Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c80a7ae2-9c00-489e-9791-6d7d4f11536f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
