{"parentUuid":"ea9f63be-4747-4e9d-a6ca-4cc24a808217","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccrxq3uGC8scfBQxqptnW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 16 pass. Now let's write the progress file, then run the perf test."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_read_input_tokens":205818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":991,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccrxq1MihDymkVSqfKKow","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"3899a159-9bfa-4534-889b-6d9bc2764ac5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:33:17.322Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"3899a159-9bfa-4534-889b-6d9bc2764ac5","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccrxq3uGC8scfBQxqptnW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KDTwhoYp9Yz1HGGcNGxKKX","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\implementation-progress.md","content":"# Implementation progress — usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n\n## Status: substantially complete, finishing perf test + docs/self-check\n\n## DONE\n\nTest-first, unit-level red->green recorded per unit:\n\n- T1 CSV encoding facade: tests written+red (`tests/test_csv_export.py`, 15 cases) →\n  code (`src/api/csv_export.py`: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell`,\n  `format_window_start`, `format_total_quantity`) → green (15 passed).\n- T2 Query schema: tests written+red (`tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py`, 13 cases) →\n  code (`src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`: `UsageExportQueryParams`, reuses\n  `CustomerId`/`Metric` from `src/api/schemas/events.py`, `from`-alias +\n  `[now-90d, now+1h]` range validator) → green (13 passed).\n- T3 Repository (integration-covered per plan's test-strategy tier bias, no\n  dedicated unit file): extended `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` with\n  `UsageRollupExportRecord`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`\n  (shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper, bound params only, fixed\n  literal ORDER BY).\n- T4 Service: tests written+red (`tests/test_usage_export_service.py`, 7 cases,\n  DB mocked via monkeypatching `scoped_transaction`/`count_usage_rollups`/\n  `stream_usage_rollups`) → code (`src/services/usage_export_service.py`:\n  `prepare_export`, `stream_export_csv`, `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS=100_000`) → green\n  (7 passed). Covers AC8/AC9/AC12/AC17/AC22 at the unit tier.\n- T5 Route: `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (two-phase cap-then-stream,\n  `responses=` OpenAPI metadata for the streamed 200/422 shapes), registered in\n  `src/main.py` (`usage_export_router`, mounted between `usage_router` and\n  `quotas_router`).\n- T6 Integration: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` — 16 tests,\n  all green: header-only empty (AC12), filters incl. none-omitted-all (AC2),\n  malformed/unknown query param 422 (AC4), auth 401 + any-scope 200 (AC6),\n  tenant isolation (AC7), row cap 422 no-partial-body (AC8), deterministic\n  ordering (AC13), formula-injection end-to-end (AC10), response headers incl.\n  strict filename regex (AC11), streaming-not-buffered via a real out-of-process\n  uvicorn server (AC9 — `ASGITransport` was proven unusable for this, see\n  Note below), OpenAPI schema exposure (AC19/DAST-1), forced pre-flight COUNT\n  error -> generic 500 (AC22), and a dedicated two-principals-one-IP Tier-2\n  discriminator for this route (AC5).\n- Docs: `PROJECT.md` already updated by planning (feature description swapped\n  from quotas to CSV export) — verified, not touched further.\n\n## Note — a real bug found and fixed during integration testing\n\n`httpx.ASGITransport`'s `ASGIResponseStream.__aiter__` does\n`yield b\"\".join(self._body)` — it joins the ENTIRE response body into a single\nchunk before the test ever sees it, regardless of how many times the app\n`yield`s. This made the streaming-not-buffered sanity check meaningless against\nthe in-process `client` fixture (chunk_count was always 1, pass or fail\nindependent of real behavior). Fixed by adding a `running_server` fixture\n(out-of-process uvicorn, mirrors `tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`'s\npattern) so the test observes genuine socket-level chunk boundaries. Also hit\nthe documented `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)` requirement for the\nAC22 forced-500 test (same pattern already established in\n`tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py`'s AC19 test) — the default\n`client` fixture re-raises app exceptions instead of returning the 500\nresponse.\n\n## REMAINING (next steps if resumed)\n\n1. Run `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` (AC16 p95 sanity at\n   100k rows) — written, not yet executed/verified green.\n2. Docs: update `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`,\n   `src/repositories/README.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` with the new\n   route/service/repo entries (plan's \"Files affected\" docs list) — not yet\n   done.\n3. Full test suite run (`pytest --cov=src --cov-branch`) to confirm >=85%\n   coverage and no regressions in existing suites.\n4. Pre-report self-check: `git diff HEAD --name-only` / untracked files vs.\n   plan's Files-affected list; grep for hardcoded secrets, missing RLS scoping,\n   unsanitized inputs across changed files.\n5. Write `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` (new entry points / trust boundaries /\n   data flows / privilege surface for this change).\n6. Final report to the coordinator.\n\nNo migration needed (plan: `migration_added: false`, read-only feature, no\nnew stored data). No `infra/` change.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_read_input_tokens":205818,"output_tokens":2020,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":991},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":2020,"cache_read_input_tokens":205818,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":991,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccrxq1MihDymkVSqfKKow","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"fb220766-3c88-45af-b85f-945d8d78dfef","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:33:36.002Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionI