{"parentUuid":"33bf70f6-63a1-4cdf-9db1-4006e7ca7a98","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry56HXXQGHGk3hhtWjf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":220240,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":617,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry54kkdq1U8Zr8oWKWi","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"88de694c-2e18-4d5b-82f9-2f0d303ed683","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:36:31.784Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"88de694c-2e18-4d5b-82f9-2f0d303ed683","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry56HXXQGHGk3hhtWjf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PK3Uvbp2jyGBSk5qye32Jn","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md","old_string":"| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |","new_string":"| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/usage_export.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` handler; two-phase pre-flight row-cap check (`usage_export_service.prepare_export`) then a `StreamingResponse` body (`usage_export_service.stream_export_csv`). Kept in its own module so `usage.py` stays untouched. Declares explicit `responses=` OpenAPI metadata (200 `text/csv`, 422) since a `StreamingResponse` has no `response_model` to introspect. |\n| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. Also the `CustomerId`/`Metric` anchored-allowlist `constr` types reused by `schemas/usage.py` and `schemas/usage_export.py`. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `schemas/usage_export.py` | `UsageExportQueryParams` for GET /v1/usage/export — optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters (`from` aliased from the `from_` field name), `[now-90d, now+1h]` range bound, `extra='forbid'`. |\n| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n| `csv_export.py` | The CSV encoding facade for the export route: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell` (OWASP formula-injection escape applied at the sink), and `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatters. |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":220240,"output_tokens":1590,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":617},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1590,"cache_read_input_tokens":220240,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":617,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry54kkdq1U8Zr8oWKWi","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"e50030b1-d59f-4daa-8e1d-ec443a132eef","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:36:40.102Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"