{"parentUuid":"01170e59-f44e-4c11-9699-80abd5b4f47c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry69z3pK3hdUJdrV9Pu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CgcGvCwd1yid6ourFdiCn3","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1657,"cache_read_input_tokens":220857,"output_tokens":168,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1657},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":168,"cache_read_input_tokens":220857,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1657,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry684xmdCq3x634ZTH2","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"8a91b36f-44fd-42a1-b8f3-daba0829285e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:36:43.668Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"8a91b36f-44fd-42a1-b8f3-daba0829285e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CgcGvCwd1yid6ourFdiCn3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/api/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tHTTP API layer: FastAPI route handlers, request/response schemas (Pydantic v2), error envelope boundary, and edge-concern middleware (request ID, security headers, CORS, body-size guards).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n12\t| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n13\t| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n14\t| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n15\t| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n16\t| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n17\t| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n18\t| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT). |\n19\t| `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. `AppError` lets a raised exception carry an explicit `app_code` (e.g. `quota_exceeded`) that overrides the default status->code map — needed because 429 is shared by two distinct codes (`rate_limited` vs `quota_exceeded`). |\n20\t\n21\t## Relationships\n22\t\n23\t**Public surface:**\n24\t- Imported by `src/main.py` to register routes with FastAPI.\n25\t- Exposes `get_app()` function which returns the fully-configured FastAPI instance.\n26\t\n27\t**Dependencies:**\n28\t- `middleware.py` and `errors.py` are registered once at app construction (middleware stack + exception handler).\n29\t- Each route handler uses `require_api_key` guard from `src/auth` to enforce authentication.\n30\t- Route handlers call `src/services.{events_service, usage_service}` to execute business logic.\n31\t- Schemas validate request bodies/parameters; malformed input raises Pydantic `ValidationError` → 422.\n32\t- Middleware and error boundary run for all routes, ensuring every response has proper headers and envelope shape.\n33\t\n34\t**Middleware ordering (in `main.py`):**\n35\t1. Request-ID / trace (outermost) — sets correlation context for all downstream logging.\n36\t2. Security headers — applied to every response.\n37\t3. CORS — explicit allowlist from config.\n38\t4. Body-size guard — reject Content-Length > 8 KiB.\n39\t5. Tier-1 edge throttle (pre-auth) — IP+route keyed.\n40\t6. `require_api_key` guard — auth.\n41\t7. Tier-2 per-key throttle (post-auth) — api_key_id keyed.\n42\t8. Route handler (innermost) — wrapped by error-envelope boundary.\n43\t\n44\t## Notes\n45\t\n46\t**Contract enforcement:**\n47\t- Request bodies are validated against Pydantic schemas; `extra='forbid'` rejects unknown fields.\n48\t- All string fields are bounded length (e.g., `customer_id` ≤128, `metric` ≤64).\n49\t- `quantity` is a decimal > 0 (no zero or negative); `idempotency_key` is alphanumeric + underscore/dash.\n50\t- GET `/v1/usage` requires a timezone-aware ISO-8601 `window` parameter within 90 days past to 1 hour future (naive datetimes rejected).\n51\t- PUT `/v1/quotas`: `limit_per_window` is an integer `>= 1` (`<= 1e15`, BIGINT-safe); `customer_id`/`metric` reuse the same anchored allowlists as events; unknown fields (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`/`scope`) are rejected outright.\n52\t\n53\t**Error handling:**\n54\t- Authentication failures (missing/invalid key) → 401/403 before handlers run.\n55\t- `PUT /v1/quotas` from a non-`admin`-scoped key → 403 `forbidden` (function-level authorization, checked in the route's composed dependency).\n56\t- Rate-limit exceeded (Tier-1 or Tier-2) → 429 `rate_limited` + Retry-After header.\n57\t- `POST /v1/events` over its quota → 429 `quota_exceeded` (distinct code, same status) + Retry-After to the next hour boundary; no event/rollup written (transaction rolled back).\n58\t- Schema validation failure → 422 with Pydantic error detail.\n59\t- Database errors (constraint violation, connection drop) → caught by error envelope → 500 (generic message, safe).\n60\t- Any unhandled exception → error envelope → 500, safe, no leak.\n61\t\n62\t**Security headers (all responses):**\n63\t- `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` (production only; localhost omitted).\n64\t- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` — disable MIME sniffing.\n65\t- `X-Frame-Options: DENY` — no embedding in iframes.\n66\t- `Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0` (API, not HTML).\n67\t"}]},"uuid":"c71b1f6c-e6df-48b7-be05-bc2d71aa3a9c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:36:43.685Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8a91b36f-44fd-42a1-b8f3-daba0829285e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"c71b1f6c-e6df-48b7-be05-bc2d71aa3a9c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry6QQU7EGALzgHLpVSd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can apply the edit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2219,"cache_read_input_tokens":222514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2219,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry6NYbomg5KWq55DziC","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ac06c856-3c74-452e-b88e-6be87045bfe4","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:36:45.336Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"ac06c856-3c74-452e-b88e-6be87045bfe4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry6QQU7EGALzgHLpVSd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017eh1MmWEbgQxeKXvhS2Fcn","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md","old_string":"| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |","new_string":"| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/usage_export.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` handler; two-phase pre-flight row-cap check (`usage_export_service.prepare_export`) then a `StreamingResponse` body (`usage_export_service.stream_export_csv`). Kept in its own module (not added to `usage.py`) so `GET /v1/usage`'s code path stays untouched. Declares explicit `responses=` OpenAPI metadata (200 `text/csv`, 422) since a `StreamingResponse` has no `response_model` to introspect. |\n| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. Also defines the `CustomerId`/`Metric` anchored-allowlist `constr` types reused by `schemas/usage.py` and `schemas/usage_export.py`. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `schemas/usage_export.py` | `UsageExportQueryParams` for GET /v1/usage/export — optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters (`from` bound via a Pydantic alias to the `from_` field, since `from` is a Python keyword), the same `[now-90d, now+1h]` range bound as `usage.py`, `extra='forbid'`. |\n| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n| `csv_export.py` | The CSV encoding facade for the export route: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell` (the OWASP CSV/formula-injection escape, applied at the encoding sink independent of upstream ingest validation), and the `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatters. |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2219,"cache_read_input_tokens":222514,"output_tokens":1338,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2219},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1338,"cache_read_input_tokens":222514,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2219,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2219,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry6NYbomg5KWq55DziC","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"a81f6a2e-66f1-4c11-8e14-1ced41