{"parentUuid":"8a2d3603-8844-46ab-b34d-e14af66d43d6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","content":"<tool_use_error>File has not been read yet. Read it first before writing to it.</tool_use_error>","is_error":true,"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hijrme3JFcPDk7Pd9tdimh"}]},"uuid":"e74903ae-6f47-402a-a878-220ea4de5348","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:37:15.717Z","toolUseResult":"Error: File has not been read yet. Read it first before writing to it.","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8a2d3603-8844-46ab-b34d-e14af66d43d6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"e74903ae-6f47-402a-a878-220ea4de5348","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry8m8DUba5kTCYnNAmw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MXC11qeA4wViHDPdLZnooA","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":612,"cache_read_input_tokens":227556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":612,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":68,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry8jQXJTkZEdhZZtNEx","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"54f88cf9-b787-4622-b8fe-0b41eac403d4","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:37:17.813Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"54f88cf9-b787-4622-b8fe-0b41eac403d4","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MXC11qeA4wViHDPdLZnooA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/services/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tBusiness logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity), usage aggregation, and time-window calculations. Orchestrates repositories and enforces domain invariants.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_service.py` | `create_event(principal, payload)` — inserts an event, checks the caller's quota (if any) on the winning-insert branch, and increments the hourly counter, all in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Raises `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`) when `R + Q > L`, which rolls back the event insert. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n12\t| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n13\t| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n14\t| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by all three services. |\n15\t\n16\t## Relationships\n17\t\n18\t**Public surface:**\n19\t- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n20\t\n21\t**Dependencies:**\n22\t- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n23\t- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n24\t- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n25\t- All three services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs.\n26\t- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n27\t\n28\t**Transaction boundary:**\n29\t- `create_event` wraps the event insert, the quota check, and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n30\t- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`) and the quota check passes, the counter increments exactly once.\n31\t- If the insert loses (duplicate key), the quota is never consulted and neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n32\t- If the quota check rejects (`R + Q > L`), raising `QuotaExceededError` propagates out of the transaction context and rolls it back — the event insert is undone and the counter is never touched (no partial write).\n33\t- `upsert_tenant_quota` wraps the quota upsert in its own transaction; a single `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0)` reports create-vs-replace with no second round-trip.\n34\t\n35\t## Notes\n36\t\n37\t**Idempotency guarantee:**\n38\t- The unique constraint `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` on the `events` table is the source of truth.\n39\t- Exactly one of N concurrent identical requests will succeed; the rest get a duplicate-key constraint violation (caught, no exception raised to handler) and fall through to a replay branch.\n40\t- The replay branch reads the original event from the table and returns it, so the caller sees a consistent result across retries.\n41\t- Recorded in the plan as the **AC-CONCURRENCY** mechanism: 50 concurrent same-key POSTs produce exactly one row and 49 get the replay response (200 vs. 201).\n42\t\n43\t**Counter atomicity:**\n44\t- The event insert and the rollup upsert are in one transaction, so both commit or both roll back.\n45\t- This means a counter never gets incremented without the event being persisted (no partial writes).\n46\t- Also means a duplicate event never increments the counter (no double-counting).\n47\t- The counter uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` with `total_quantity + EXCLUDED.total_quantity` to handle the increment (PostgreSQL's row-level conflict resolution, atomic at the SQL level).\n48\t\n49\t**Time-window semantics:**\n50\t- A timestamp is floored to its hour (UTC) to get the `window_start`. E.g., `2026-07-06T14:35:42Z` → `2026-07-06T14:00:00Z`.\n51\t- The floor is done explicitly in Python (`ts.replace(minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)`) rather than in the database, because PostgreSQL's `date_trunc('hour', ts)` is STABLE (depends on session timezone), not IMMUTABLE, so it cannot be used in a stored generated column.\n52\t- All windows are in UTC; clients must provide timezone-aware ISO-8601 timestamps on GET.\n53\t\n54\t**Scoping by api_key_id:**\n55\t- Both services receive the authenticated `api_key_id` from the route guard (set in `request.state`).\n56\t- Both services pass it to the repository layer, which includes it in the WHERE clause (e.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id`).\n57\t- This is the primary RLS mechanism; the PostgreSQL RLS policy is the backstop.\n58\t"}]},"uuid":"0a1237ab-2269-4c4b-97b4-667d39392ac7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:37:17.837Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"54f88cf9-b787-4622-b8fe-0b41eac403d4","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"0a1237ab-2269-4c4b-97b4-667d39392ac7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccry8xYJo5Knh1PrPgxRk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MTQEjSnusi2nGYS3PNvniw","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md","old_string":"| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by all three services. |\n\n## Relationships\n\n**Public surface:**\n- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n- All three services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs.\n- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.","new_string":"| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n| `usage_export_service.py` | `prepare_export(principal, params)` — the pre-flight row-cap check: a `COUNT(*)` in its own transaction, raising a plain 422 `HTTPException` over `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS` (100,000) *before* any response byte; any other (non-cap) error propagates uncaught to the error-envelope boundary (fail-closed 500, no stream ever started). `stream_export_csv(principal, params)` — the `StreamingResponse` body generator: opens its own tenant-scoped transaction (Starlette pulls it only after the route returns), yields the header row first always (so an empty result is a 200 header-only CSV, never 404), then one CSV-encoded row per streamed rollup at constant memory (a reused `io.StringIO`, drained and reset per row), and logs one `usage.export` audit event in a `finally` block (fires even on a client disconnect or a mid-stream error). |\n| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by all three counter-facing services. |\n\n## Relationships\n\n**Public surface:**\n- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, usage_export, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n- `usage_export_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` (`count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`) and `src/api/csv_export.py` (the column contract + formula-escape facade) — it owns the `csv.writer`/`io.StringIO` streaming mechanics, `csv_export.py` owns only the encoding/escaping contract.\n- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n- All services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs (the export has no scope gate — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data).\n- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2058,"cache_read_input_tokens":228168,"output_tokens":1653,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2058},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1653,"cache_read_input_tokens":228168,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2058,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2058,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccry8vzY976u73WyEFt17","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"bb30dc05-7a03-40f0-9c04-fb6cc1125c48","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:37:32.743Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
