{"parentUuid":"ab8086cd-b86b-4778-85c7-74598b11fb94","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcryCC8x3j5rxs1SCtWgC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Q9MK11MA5QHK2yu86fanFr","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","offset":1,"limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":729,"cache_read_input_tokens":236036,"output_tokens":152,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":729},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":152,"cache_read_input_tokens":236036,"cache_creation_input_tokens":729,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":729,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcryCAf9hqRJ1ctpUynh9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"9da93eac-d5bb-44ac-a23e-5761e6eb8362","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:05.689Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"9da93eac-d5bb-44ac-a23e-5761e6eb8362","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q9MK11MA5QHK2yu86fanFr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly — system architecture\n2\t\n3\t## Overview\n4\t\n5\tMeterly ingests metered usage events, serves aggregated per-customer/metric\n6\tcounters, and enforces admin-set per-customer, per-metric usage caps\n7\t(\"quotas\"). Three authenticated HTTP endpoints, one PostgreSQL database, one\n8\tRedis rate-limit store, running as a Docker container on ECS Fargate behind an ALB.\n9\t\n10\t```\n11\tClient --HTTPS+API key--> ALB --> FastAPI (ECS Fargate, >=2 tasks)\n12\t                                     |-- Tier-1 (IP) / Tier-2 (api_key_id) throttle --> Redis\n13\t                                     |-- bound-parameter SQL, RLS-scoped -------------> RDS PostgreSQL\n14\t                                     |-- DB credential fetch ------------------------> Secrets Manager\n15\t                                     |-- traces/logs/errors -------------------------> CloudWatch/X-Ray/Sentry\n16\t```\n17\t\n18\t```mermaid\n19\tflowchart LR\n20\t    Client[Client] -->|\"HTTPS + API key\"| ALB[ALB]\n21\t    ALB --> FastAPI[\"FastAPI (ECS Fargate, >=2 tasks)\"]\n22\t    FastAPI -->|\"Tier-1 IP+route / Tier-2 api_key_id throttle\"| Redis[(Redis)]\n23\t    FastAPI -->|\"require_api_key: cache hit or Argon2id verify\"| AuthDB[(RDS PostgreSQL: api_keys)]\n24\t    FastAPI -->|\"POST /v1/events: insert + quota check + rollup upsert\"| EventsDB[(RDS PostgreSQL: events / usage_rollup / quotas)]\n25\t    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB\n26\t    FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB\n27\t    FastAPI -->|\"DB credential fetch\"| Secrets[Secrets Manager]\n28\t    FastAPI -->|\"traces/logs/errors\"| Observability[\"CloudWatch / X-Ray / Sentry\"]\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\t## Request flow — `POST /v1/events`\n32\t\n33\t1. Request-id/trace assigned, security headers queued (`src/logging/middleware.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`).\n34\t2. Tier-1 IP+route throttle (Redis token bucket; fails open on a Redis outage).\n35\t3. `require_api_key` — split-token parse, in-process verification-cache check,\n36\t   falling back to a DB lookup + Argon2id verify on a cache miss\n37\t   (`src/auth/__init__.py`, `src/auth/api_key.py`).\n38\t4. Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` throttle (`src/auth/rate_limit.py`).\n39\t5. Pydantic schema validation (`src/api/schemas/events.py`) — anchored\n40\t   allowlists, `extra='forbid'`.\n41\t6. `events_service.create_event` — one transaction:\n42\t   `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING`, and only\n43\t   if a row was inserted:\n44\t   - the quota check: `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` locks the caller's\n45\t     quota row for `(customer, metric)` (if one exists) and reads the\n46\t     current-window rollup total fresh; if `R + Q > L` the service raises\n47\t     `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`, `Retry-After` to the next\n48\t     hour boundary), which propagates out of the transaction and rolls back\n49\t     the event insert — no partial write, no rollup increment\n50\t     (`src/services/events_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`).\n51\t   - otherwise, `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` the `usage_rollup`\n52\t     counter (`src/repositories/events_repo.py`).\n53\t   A duplicate `idempotency_key` (replay) never reaches the quota check at\n54\t   all — only the winning-insert branch does.\n55\t7. Error-envelope boundary catches anything unhandled and returns the generic\n56\t   `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` shape (`src/api/errors.py`); `AppError`\n57\t   lets a handler attach an explicit `app_code` (e.g. `quota_exceeded`) that\n58\t   overrides the default status->code map, so two different 429s\n59\t   (`rate_limited` vs. `quota_exceeded`) stay distinguishable to the caller.\n60\t\n61\t## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage`\n62\t\n63\tSame auth/throttle/error stack; the service floors `window` to the UTC hour\n64\tand reads a single `usage_rollup` row scoped by the caller's `api_key_id`\n65\t(`src/services/usage_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`). A missing\n66\tbucket returns zeros with 200, never 404.\n67\t\n68\t## Request flow — `PUT /v1/quotas`\n69\t\n70\tAdmin-scoped create-or-replace of a per-customer, per-metric usage cap.\n71\tAuth -> Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` throttle -> an `admin`-scope assertion in the\n72\troute's composed dependency (403 `forbidden` for a non-admin key) -> schema\n73\tvalidation (`src/api/schemas/quotas.py`) -> `upsert_tenant_quota`, a single\n74\t`INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ...\n75\tRETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted` that reports create-vs-replace in one\n76\tround-trip (201 create / 200 replace), with a `quota.upsert` audit log\n77\t(`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`,\n78\t`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`).\n79\t\n80\t## Data model\n81\t\n82\t- `api_keys` — the tenant/credential table (migration 0001), extended with a\n83\t  `scope` column (migration 0003: `'ingest'` default, `'admin'` elevated).\n84\t  `secret_hash` is Argon2id; `key_id` is the public split-token lookup\n85\t  handle. `scope='admin'` is a superset scope — an admin key does everything\n86\t  an ingest key does, plus call `PUT /v1/quotas`; a tenant that wants quotas\n87\t  provisions one admin-scoped key and uses it for both.\n88\t- `events` — append-only ingest log (migration 0001). `UNIQUE (api_key_id,\n89\t  idempotency_key)` is the idempotency guarantee; RLS policy\n90\t  `events_tenant_isolation` is the application-scoping backstop.\n91\t- `usage_rollup` — derived hourly aggregate (migration 0002, expand +\n92\t  backfill from `events`). Composite PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric,\n93\t  window_start)`; RLS policy `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation`.\n94\t- `quotas` — per-tenant, per-customer, per-metric usage caps (migration\n95\t  0003). PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`; `CHECK (limit_per_window >=\n96\t  1)`; RLS policy `quotas_tenant_isolation`. The `POST /v1/events` quota\n97\t  check takes `FOR UPDATE` on this row to serialize concurrent writers for\n98\t  the same `(customer, metric)` — see *Quota enforcement / atomicity* below.\n99\t\n100\t## Quota enforcement / atomicity"}]},"uuid":"eb870a4c-a4d2-476d-be42-08f643b19a94","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:05.703Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9da93eac-d5bb-44ac-a23e-5761e6eb8362","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
