{"parentUuid":"e72bfcdb-b376-48f5-9c0e-3cfa777ec095","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcryCz5CBxTiCCj1Sm5XN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019G7mhxYuBhyAChX7TCMQYN","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","old_string":"    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB","new_string":"    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage: read rollup\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"GET /v1/usage/export: pre-flight COUNT + streamed SELECT\"| EventsDB\n    FastAPI -->|\"PUT /v1/quotas: upsert cap\"| EventsDB"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":582,"cache_read_input_tokens":239586,"output_tokens":335,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":582},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":335,"cache_read_input_tokens":239586,"cache_creation_input_tokens":582,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":582,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcryCxXvBhHM71s35UxBD","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"9e43910d-48ad-4ce4-8174-2cba95b3fee7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:16.903Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"9e43910d-48ad-4ce4-8174-2cba95b3fee7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019G7mhxYuBhyAChX7TCMQYN","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"36de7cca-5e67-4cc0-a4e6-1d3878b88267","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:17.955Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9e43910d-48ad-4ce4-8174-2cba95b3fee7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"36de7cca-5e67-4cc0-a4e6-1d3878b88267","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcryDQ2r1xWoLTNv76zcQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Rp82GfND1HDDnBnGNbc8b","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","old_string":"## Request flow — `PUT /v1/quotas`","new_string":"## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage/export`\n\nSame auth/throttle/error stack, plus a two-phase pre-flight-then-stream\ndesign (`src/api/routes/usage_export.py`,\n`src/services/usage_export_service.py`,\n`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`):\n\n1. `UsageExportQueryParams` validates the optional `customer_id`/`metric`/\n   `from`/`to` filters (`src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`) — reuses the same\n   `CustomerId`/`Metric` anchored allowlists as `events.py` and the same\n   `[now-90d, now+1h]` bound idiom as `usage.py`'s `window`, applied here to\n   a `[from, to]` range.\n2. **Pre-flight cap check** (`prepare_export`): a `COUNT(*)` over the\n   caller's rows (scoped by `api_key_id` first, plus the optional filters)\n   inside its own transaction. Over 100,000 rows -> 422\n   `validation_failed`, logged at `warn` (`usage.export.rejected`). This\n   runs, and fully resolves, *before* any response byte — once a\n   `StreamingResponse` is constructed the status line is already 200 and the\n   cap decision can no longer cleanly 422. Any *other* (non-cap) error here\n   propagates uncaught to the error-envelope boundary: a fail-closed generic\n   500, transaction rolled back, no stream ever started.\n3. **Stream** (`stream_export_csv`): a `StreamingResponse` whose body\n   generator is pulled by Starlette only after the handler returns, so it\n   opens its **own** tenant-scoped transaction (the `SET LOCAL\n   app.current_api_key_id` RLS-backstop setting and the server-side cursor\n   both need to stay valid for the whole stream, not just the pre-flight\n   phase). Yields the header row first, always (an empty result is a 200\n   header-only CSV, never 404), then one CSV-encoded row per record from\n   `stream_usage_rollups` (`ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric` — a\n   fixed literal, never client-derived — `LIMIT 100000`), each row written\n   into a reused `io.StringIO` via stdlib `csv.writer` (RFC 4180, CRLF,\n   `QUOTE_MINIMAL`) and drained to bytes immediately — constant memory\n   throughout. `customer_id`/`metric` text cells pass through\n   `src/api/csv_export.py`'s `escape_csv_text_cell` (the OWASP\n   formula-injection defense: a leading `= + - @ \\t \\r` gets a `'` prefix)\n   *before* reaching the writer; numeric/timestamp cells are formatted but\n   never escaped (they're server-generated, never attacker-controlled).\n   Logs exactly one `usage.export` audit event in a `finally` block\n   (`rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — never the\n   raw `customer_id`/`metric` values), so a client disconnect or a mid-stream\n   DB error still records what was actually sent.\n\nResponse headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`,\n`Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\"usage-export-<UTC\ntimestamp>.csv\"` (no tenant identifier in the filename), plus the inherited\n`nosniff` and (via the existing `/v1/usage`-prefix rule in\n`src/api/middleware.py`) `Cache-Control: no-store`.\n\n**Accepted risk — mid-stream failure truncates the CSV.** Once the 200\nstatus line and header bytes are on the wire, an unhandled error partway\nthrough the stream can no longer be converted to a clean error envelope; the\nclient sees a truncated download it can re-request. This is strictly the\n*post-200* case — the pre-flight `COUNT` phase above is fully recoverable\nand does return the generic 500 envelope. Bounded by the row cap + Tier-2\nthrottle + connection-pool sizing; batched keyset pagination is the future\nmitigation if this needs closing further.\n\n## Request flow — `PUT /v1/quotas`"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":412,"cache_read_input_tokens":240168,"output_tokens":1577,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":412},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1577,"cache_read_input_tokens":240168,"cache_creation_input_tokens":412,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":412,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcryDMTopedGFeeon2txf","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"089cb301-f61c-489c-96f5-3a51f14ed7be","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:34.496Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
