{"parentUuid":"e79d65ab-3f1b-453c-8818-7c3b1a5b2389","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"42022266-80ed-4b1b-af25-460921b78a21","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UqcRUBj2wHfrbD1MXRodtV","type":"tool_result","content":"224\t(encryption at rest, private subnets, least-privilege IAM, no `BYPASSRLS`).\n225\t\n226\t## Known deviations / accepted risks\n227\t\n228\tSee `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` for the rate-limit fail-open behavior and the\n229\tOTel/Sentry wiring-at-construction-time change vs. the plan's original\n230\tlifespan-hook placement. See `plan.md`'s \"Open questions\" section for the\n231\taccepted risks around key-revocation latency, `api_key_id`-as-tenant-scope,\n232\tand the Postgres app-role bootstrap's CI-network-reachability prerequisite.\n233\t"}]},"uuid":"f51c0a8e-4935-482d-93f3-5a6b2ba32c4b","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:42.326Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e79d65ab-3f1b-453c-8818-7c3b1a5b2389","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"f51c0a8e-4935-482d-93f3-5a6b2ba32c4b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcryFBowVmzbCAYibu4Tf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NonMFmP7SbEU9kP7khBqDq","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","old_string":"## Known deviations / accepted risks\n\nSee `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` for the rate-limit fail-open behavior and the\nOTel/Sentry wiring-at-construction-time change vs. the plan's original\nlifespan-hook placement. See `plan.md`'s \"Open questions\" section for the\naccepted risks around key-revocation latency, `api_key_id`-as-tenant-scope,\nand the Postgres app-role bootstrap's CI-network-reachability prerequisite.","new_string":"## Known deviations / accepted risks\n\nSee `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` for the rate-limit fail-open behavior and the\nOTel/Sentry wiring-at-construction-time change vs. the plan's original\nlifespan-hook placement. See `plan.md`'s \"Open questions\" section for the\naccepted risks around key-revocation latency, `api_key_id`-as-tenant-scope,\nand the Postgres app-role bootstrap's CI-network-reachability prerequisite.\n\n**`GET /v1/usage/export` p95 measurement vs. the documented 500ms target\n(plan §\"Open questions\" #1, unresolved — flagged, not silently accepted).**\n`tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` measures real p95 latency for\na full 100,000-row export end to end (real Postgres testcontainer, in-process\nASGI transport) rather than asserting the documented 500ms budget, per the\nproject's existing honest-disclosure convention\n(`tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`). The measured p95 in this sandboxed\ndev environment was **~9.8 seconds** — far outside the documented 500ms\ntarget, driven by per-row Python-level CSV encoding/formatting/escaping and\ngenerator overhead across 100,000 rows, not primarily DB query time (the\npre-flight `COUNT` and the bounded 100k-row sort are both fast). This is a\nreal architectural cost of the per-row stdlib-`csv` streaming design the plan\nchose (constant memory, single DB snapshot) traded against raw throughput at\nthe row cap; it is not an artifact of this specific sandboxed run alone. The\nplan explicitly left the 500ms number as an *open, unconfirmed* target\npending checkpoint confirmation — this measurement is the data point that\nconfirms or adjusts it. Follow-up options if 500ms is confirmed as binding:\nbatch multiple rows per `csv.writer` flush, or reconsider the per-row\nescape/format call overhead; out of scope for this slice to change\nunilaterally since the plan fixed the streaming design."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":363,"cache_read_input_tokens":242832,"output_tokens":1022,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":363},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1022,"cache_read_input_tokens":242832,"cache_creation_input_tokens":363,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":363,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcryF82j6KKRqU8PG96Gr","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"784f68df-6f7b-462e-99bb-8d57415ea74a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:38:53.711Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
