{"parentUuid":"abba53fa-13da-4c11-8a13-cb161932362a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccrz5jiuccYDyxogT3Uku","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014sQ9kVrgqzxpKzL8emjTrQ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\implementation-progress.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257313,"cache_read_input_tokens":13319,"output_tokens":476,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":257313},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":476,"cache_read_input_tokens":13319,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257313,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":257313,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"messages_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":214973}}},"requestId":"req_011Ccrz5hbfXr3AmhEzr9ugu","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"bc474a3b-c66d-4c35-bc77-14927d27d8e8","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:49:49.284Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"bc474a3b-c66d-4c35-bc77-14927d27d8e8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"31f803c6-6a83-48a3-9c6d-815c29da9dd0","agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014sQ9kVrgqzxpKzL8emjTrQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation progress — usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n2\t\n3\t## Status: COMPLETE — all planned files written, full suite green (178 passed, 88% coverage), docs updated, self-check done, surface-delta.md written.\n4\t\n5\t## DONE\n6\t\n7\tTest-first, unit-level red->green recorded per unit:\n8\t\n9\t- T1 CSV encoding facade: tests written+red (`tests/test_csv_export.py`, 15 cases) →\n10\t  code (`src/api/csv_export.py`: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell`,\n11\t  `format_window_start`, `format_total_quantity`) → green (15 passed).\n12\t- T2 Query schema: tests written+red (`tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py`, 13 cases) →\n13\t  code (`src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`: `UsageExportQueryParams`, reuses\n14\t  `CustomerId`/`Metric` from `src/api/schemas/events.py`, `from`-alias +\n15\t  `[now-90d, now+1h]` range validator) → green (13 passed).\n16\t- T3 Repository (integration-covered per plan's test-strategy tier bias, no\n17\t  dedicated unit file): extended `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` with\n18\t  `UsageRollupExportRecord`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`\n19\t  (shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper, bound params only, fixed\n20\t  literal ORDER BY).\n21\t- T4 Service: tests written+red (`tests/test_usage_export_service.py`, 7 cases,\n22\t  DB mocked via monkeypatching `scoped_transaction`/`count_usage_rollups`/\n23\t  `stream_usage_rollups`) → code (`src/services/usage_export_service.py`:\n24\t  `prepare_export`, `stream_export_csv`, `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS=100_000`) → green\n25\t  (7 passed). Covers AC8/AC9/AC12/AC17/AC22 at the unit tier.\n26\t- T5 Route: `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (two-phase cap-then-stream,\n27\t  `responses=` OpenAPI metadata for the streamed 200/422 shapes), registered in\n28\t  `src/main.py` (`usage_export_router`, mounted between `usage_router` and\n29\t  `quotas_router`).\n30\t- T6 Integration: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` — 16 tests,\n31\t  all green: header-only empty (AC12), filters incl. none-omitted-all (AC2),\n32\t  malformed/unknown query param 422 (AC4), auth 401 + any-scope 200 (AC6),\n33\t  tenant isolation (AC7), row cap 422 no-partial-body (AC8), deterministic\n34\t  ordering (AC13), formula-injection end-to-end (AC10), response headers incl.\n35\t  strict filename regex (AC11), streaming-not-buffered via a real out-of-process\n36\t  uvicorn server (AC9 — `ASGITransport` was proven unusable for this, see\n37\t  Note below), OpenAPI schema exposure (AC19/DAST-1), forced pre-flight COUNT\n38\t  error -> generic 500 (AC22), and a dedicated two-principals-one-IP Tier-2\n39\t  discriminator for this route (AC5).\n40\t- Docs: `PROJECT.md` already updated by planning (feature description swapped\n41\t  from quotas to CSV export) — verified, not touched further.\n42\t\n43\t## Note — a real bug found and fixed during integration testing\n44\t\n45\t`httpx.ASGITransport`'s `ASGIResponseStream.__aiter__` does\n46\t`yield b\"\".join(self._body)` — it joins the ENTIRE response body into a single\n47\tchunk before the test ever sees it, regardless of how many times the app\n48\t`yield`s. This made the streaming-not-buffered sanity check meaningless against\n49\tthe in-process `client` fixture (chunk_count was always 1, pass or fail\n50\tindependent of real behavior). Fixed by adding a `running_server` fixture\n51\t(out-of-process uvicorn, mirrors `tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`'s\n52\tpattern) so the test observes genuine socket-level chunk boundaries. Also hit\n53\tthe documented `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)` requirement for the\n54\tAC22 forced-500 test (same pattern already established in\n55\t`tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py`'s AC19 test) — the default\n56\t`client` fixture re-raises app exceptions instead of returning the 500\n57\tresponse.\n58\t\n59\t## REMAINING (next steps if resumed)\n60\t\n61\t1. Run `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` (AC16 p95 sanity at\n62\t   100k rows) — written, not yet executed/verified green.\n63\t2. Docs: update `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`,\n64\t   `src/repositories/README.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` with the new\n65\t   route/service/repo entries (plan's \"Files affected\" docs list) — not yet\n66\t   done.\n67\t3. Full test suite run (`pytest --cov=src --cov-branch`) to confirm >=85%\n68\t   coverage and no regressions in existing suites.\n69\t4. Pre-report self-check: `git diff HEAD --name-only` / untracked files vs.\n70\t   plan's Files-affected list; grep for hardcoded secrets, missing RLS scoping,\n71\t   unsanitized inputs across changed files.\n72\t5. Write `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` (new entry points / trust boundaries /\n73\t   data flows / privilege surface for this change).\n74\t6. Final report to the coordinator.\n75\t\n76\tNo migration needed (plan: `migration_added: false`, read-only feature, no\n77\tnew stored data). No `infra/` change.\n78\t"}]},"uuid":"8f7aab8a-cfaa-443d-9e66-20d5f8f20d94","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:49:49.300Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bc474a3b-c66d-4c35-bc77-14927d27d8e8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"8f7aab8a-cfaa-443d-9e66-20d5f8f20d94","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccrz6JgYfqNTnL8LKMBtr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me rewrite this fully to reflect the true completed state (the \"REMAINING\" section is stale — all items are actually done)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":62,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2554,"cache_read_input_tokens":270632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2554,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccrz6HEVFM6raC3659bDs","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"173f3e4f-b394-420d-a8d6-54fe4ac995f7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:49:51.663Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"173f3e4f-b394-420d-a8d6-54fe4ac995f7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccrz6JgYfqNTnL8LKMBtr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RhX3AHuWKr2B5wgnx7iehN","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\implementation-progress.md","content":"# Implementation progress — usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n\n## Status: COMPLETE\n\nAll plan items built, all tests green, docs updated, self-check done,\nsurface-delta.md written. Ready for the coordinator's final report / handoff\nto testing.\n\n## DONE\n\nTest-first, unit-level red->green recorded per unit:\n\n- T1 CSV encoding facade: tests written+red (`tests/test_csv_export.py`, 15 cases) →\n  code (`src/api/csv_export.py`: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell`,\n  `format_window_start`, `format_total_quantity`) → green (15 passed).\n- T2 Query schema: tests written+red (`tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py`, 13 cases) →\n  code (`src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`: `UsageExportQueryParams`, reuses\n  `CustomerId`/`Metric` from `src/api/schemas/events.py`, `from`-alias +\n  `[now-90d, now+1h]` range validator) → green (13 passed).\n- T3 Repository (integration-covered per plan's test-strategy tier bias, no\n  dedicated unit file): extended `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` with\n  `UsageRollupExportRecord`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`\n  (shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper, bound params only, fixed\n  literal ORDER BY).\n- T4 Service: tests written+red (`tests/test_usage_export_service.py`, 7 cases,\n  DB mocked via monkeypatching `scoped_transaction`/`count_usage_rollups`/\n  `stream_usage_rollups`) → code (`src/services/usage_export_service.py`:\n  `prepare_export`, `stream_export_csv`, `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS=100_000`) → green\n  (7 passed). Covers AC8/AC9/AC12/AC17/AC22 at the unit tier.\n- T5 Route: `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (two-phase cap-then-stream,\n  `responses=` OpenAPI metadata for the streamed 200/422 shapes), registered in\n  `src/main.py` (`usage_export_router`, mounted between `usage_router` and\n  `quotas_router`).\n- T6 Integration: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` — 18 tests,\n  all green: header-only empty (AC12), filters incl. customer_id/metric/from-to\n  and none-omitted-all (AC2), malformed/unknown query param 422 (AC4), auth 401\n  + any-scope 200 (AC6), tenant isolation (AC7), row cap 422 no-partial-body\n  (AC8), deterministic ordering (AC13), formula-injection end-to-end (AC10),\n  response headers incl. strict filename regex (AC11), streaming-not-buffered\n  via a real out-of-process uvicorn server (AC9 — `ASGITransport` was proven\n  unusable for this, see Note below), OpenAPI schema exposure (AC19/DAST-1),\n  forced pre-flight COUNT error -> generic 500 (AC22), and a dedicated\n  two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 discriminator for this route (AC5).\n- T7 Perf sanity: `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` (AC16) — green.\n  Measures real p95 at 100,000 rows and asserts correctness (full,\n  untruncated row set), following the project's `test_perf_smoke.py`\n  honest-disclosure convention rather than hard-asserting the documented\n  500ms budget (see Note below — real measured p95 is ~9.8s, far over\n  budget, an honest open finding, not silently hidden or gated on).\n- T8 Docs: updated `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`,\n  `src/repositories/README.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` (new\n  `GET /v1/usage/export` request-flow section, mermaid diagram edge, and a\n  \"Known deviations\" entry documenting the p95 finding). `PROJECT.md` was\n  already updated by planning (feature description swapped from quotas to\n  CSV export) — verified, not touched further.\n\n## Note — a real bug found and fixed during integration testing\n\n`httpx.ASGITransport`'s `ASGIResponseStream.__aiter__` does\n`yield b\"\".join(self._body)` — it joins the ENTIRE response body into a single\nchunk before the test ever sees it, regardless of how many times the app\n`yield`s. This made the streaming-not-buffered sanity check meaningless against\nthe in-process `client` fixture (chunk_count was always 1, pass or fail\nindependent of real behavior). Fixed by adding a `running_server` fixture\n(out-of-process uvicorn, mirrors `tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`'s\npattern) so the test observes genuine socket-level chunk boundaries. Also hit\nthe documented `ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False)` requirement for the\nAC22 forced-500 test (same pattern already established in\n`tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py`'s AC19 test) — the default\n`client` fixture re-raises app exceptions instead of returning the 500\nresponse.\n\n## Note — honest perf finding (AC16, plan's Open Question 1)\n\nMeasured p95 for a full 100,000-row export (real Postgres testcontainer,\nin-process ASGI) was **~9.8 seconds**, far over the plan's proposed-but-\nunconfirmed 500ms target. Root cause is per-row Python-level CSV\nencoding/escaping/formatting + generator overhead across 100k rows, not DB\nquery time (the pre-flight COUNT and the bounded sort are both fast). This is\ndisclosed in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Known deviations\" section and\nin the perf test's scratch-file measurement\n(`meterly_usage_export_perf_measurement.json`), not silently hidden. The plan\nexplicitly left the 500ms number open pending checkpoint confirmation — this\nis the data point for that decision, not a defect I introduced by deviating\nfrom the plan's chosen design (server-side cursor + stdlib `csv`, which was\nlocked in by the plan).\n\n## Verification performed this session\n\n- Full suite: `pytest tests -q --cov=src --cov-branch --deselect\n  tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py` → **178 passed, 88% coverage**\n  (gate is >=85%). `test_perf_k6_load.py` deselected consistent with existing\n  project convention (needs a k6 binary not present in this sandbox — verified\n  by running it standalone: it skips/handles absence gracefully, same as prior\n  features' runs).\n- Self-check (a): `git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others\n  --exclude-standard` — every planned create/modify file is present: `PROJECT.md`,\n  `docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`, `src/main.py`,\n  `src/repositories/README.md`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`,\n  `src/services/README.md` (modified); `src/api/csv_export.py`,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`,\n  `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, plus the 5 test files (new,\n  untracked). No planned file missing; no stray files (transient\n  `.coverage.*` worker artifacts from local test runs were deleted).\n- Self-check (b) hardcoded secrets: `grep -rniE\n  \"(api_key|apikey|token|secret|password|credentials)\\s*=\\s*['\\\"][^'\\\"]{8,}\"`\n  across all changed files → no matches.\n- Self-check (b) RLS scoping: confirmed `count_usage_rollups` and\n  `stream_usage_rollups` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`) both start their\n  WHERE clause with `api_key_id = :api_key_id` via the shared\n  `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper; `api_key_id` is sourced only from\n  `principal.api_key_id` in the service, never from client input.\n- Self-check (b) unsanitized inputs: confirmed the only new HTTP input\n  surface (`GET /v1/usage/export` query params) is bound through\n  `Annotated[UsageExportQueryParams, Query()]` in\n  `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` — schema-first, `extra=\"forbid\"`, reused\n  anchored-allowlist `constr` types for `customer_id`/`metric`.\n- Self-check (c) acceptance criteria: all 22 criteria in\n  `.pipeline/acceptance.md` are addressed — AC1-AC17, AC19-AC22 built and\n  test-covered (unit and/or integration, mapped in T1-T7 above); AC18 is\n  delegated to the security stage per the plan's frontmatter\n  (`delegated_criteria: [AC18]`), not built here by design.\n\nNo migration needed (plan: `migration_added: false`, read-only feature, no\nnew stored data). No `infra/` change. `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` already\nwritten (new entry point, new CSV-formula trust boundary, new DB queries/log\nevent, new-but-matching-existing-shape authz surface).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":62,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2554,"cache_read_input_tokens":270632,"output_tokens":3343,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2554},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":62,"output_tokens":3343,"cache_read_input_tokens":270632,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2554,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2554,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccrz6HEVFM6raC3659bDs","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"57c603be-c41b-421c-80bf-52f4099d3251","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:50:19.248Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
