{"parentUuid":"82cc6d19-2e55-4df3-816a-43d0118bfeb6","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab73956eb6c77cae9","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcrzCC9oewEeEqLsoYXRb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is confirmed complete and matches the plan's file list. Final summary:\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented `GET /v1/usage/export` per `.pipeline/plan.md`, test-first per unit (red→green recorded in `.pipeline/implementation-progress.md`).\n\n**Files created:**\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\csv_export.py` — CSV encoding facade (RFC 4180 header, OWASP formula-injection escape, value formatters)\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\schemas\\usage_export.py` — `UsageExportQueryParams`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\usage_export_service.py` — `prepare_export` (pre-flight cap, fail-closed) + `stream_export_csv` (streaming generator)\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\usage_export.py` — the route\n- Tests: `tests/test_csv_export.py`, `tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py`, `tests/test_usage_export_service.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (18 tests), `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py`\n\n**Files modified:** `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` (added `count_usage_rollups`/`stream_usage_rollups`, existing `find_usage_rollup` untouched), `src/main.py` (router registration), `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`, `src/repositories/README.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md`.\n\n**No migration, no infra change** (plan: read-only feature, no new stored data).\n\n**Verification:** Full suite `pytest --cov=src --cov-branch` → **178 passed, 88% coverage** (gate ≥85%). Self-check: diff matches plan's files-affected list exactly; no hardcoded secrets; every export query scoped by `api_key_id` first; the one new HTTP input surface is schema-validated with `extra=\"forbid\"` and reused anchored allowlists. All 22 acceptance criteria addressed (AC18 delegated to security per plan).\n\n**Two honest findings surfaced (not hidden):**\n1. A real bug in `httpx.ASGITransport` (`ASGIResponseStream.__aiter__` joins the whole body into one chunk) made the streaming-sanity check meaningless in-process — fixed by testing against a real out-of-process uvicorn server instead.\n2. **AC16 perf**: measured p95 at the 100,000-row cap is **~9.8s**, far over the plan's proposed (but explicitly unconfirmed/open) 500ms target. Root cause is per-row Python CSV encoding overhead, not DB time. Documented in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Known deviations\" section and the perf test's scratch measurement — this is the data point for the plan's Open Question 1, not something I resolved unilaterally since the plan locked in the streaming design.\n\n`.pipeline/surface-delta.md` and `.pipeline/implementation-progress.md` are written and current."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":698,"cache_read_input_tokens":279299,"output_tokens":1278,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":698},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1278,"cache_read_input_tokens":279299,"cache_creation_input_tokens":698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":698,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcrzC9DCmL9tgKq2Fzkuq","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"e7e19d01-113c-44b6-b462-5bd9aadc85c7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T18:51:24.335Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-tes